template.name: Dell PowerVault SNMP
template.description: Generated by mib2zabbix and personalized by Renan Schiavo

item.name: uNumber
item.description: The number of connectivity units present on this system (represented by this agent). May be a count of the boards in a chassis or the number of full boxes in a rack.

item.name: sysContact
item.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.

item.name: sysDescr
item.description: A textual description of the entity. This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII characters.

item.name: sysLocation
item.description: The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor').

item.name: sysName
item.description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name.

item.name: sysUpTime
item.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.

discovery_rule.name: Unit Discovery
discovery_rule.description: A connectivity unit entry containing objects for a particular unit.

item_prototype.name: Contact for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: Contact information for this connectivity unit.

item_prototype.name: UnitControl for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: This object is used to control the addressed connUnit. NOTE: 'Cold Start' and 'Warm Start' are as defined in MIB II and are not meant to be a factory reset. resetConnUnitColdStart: the addressed unit performs a 'Cold Start' reset. resetConnUnitWarmStart: the addressed unit performs a 'Warm Start' reset. offlineConnUnit: the addressed unit puts itself into an implementation dependant 'offline' state. In general,if a unit is in an offline state, it cannot be used to perform meaningful Fibre Channel work. onlineConnUnit: the addressed unit puts itself into an implementation dependant 'online' state. In general, if a unit is in an online state, it is capable of performing meaningful Fibre Channel work. NOTE: Each implementation may chose not to allow any or all of these values on a SET.

item_prototype.name: DomainId for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: 24 bit Fibre Channel address ID of this connectivity unit, right justified with leading zero's if required. If this value is not applicable, return all bits set to one.

item_prototype.name: Unit Info for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: A display string containing information about this connectivity unit. This object value should be persistent between boots.

item_prototype.name: Unit Number of Zones for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: Number of zones defined in connUnitZoneTable.

item_prototype.name: Unit Product Model Name for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: The connectivity unit vendor's product model name.

item_prototype.name: Unit Serial number for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: The serial number for this connectivity unit.

item_prototype.name: Unit Overall State for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: Overall state of the connectivity unit.

trigger_prototype.name: Overall state of {#UNITNAME} is not ok

item_prototype.name: Unit Overall Status of Connectivity for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: Overall status of the connectivity unit.

trigger_prototype.name: Overall Status of Connectivity for {#UNITNAME} is not ok

item_prototype.name: Unit UpTime for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: The number of centiseconds since the last unit initialization.

item_prototype.name: Unit Url for {#UNITNAME}
item_prototype.description: URL to launch a management application, if applicable. Otherwise empty string. In a standalone unit, this would be the same as the top-level URL. This has the same definition as systemURL for keywords.

discovery_rule.name: Unit Event Discovery
discovery_rule.description: Each entry contains information on a specific event for the given connectivity unit.

item_prototype.name: Unit Event Descr for {#EVENTID}
item_prototype.description: The description of the event.

item_prototype.name: Unit Event Severity for {#EVENTID}
item_prototype.description: The event severity level.

item_prototype.name: Unit Event Type for {#EVENTID}
item_prototype.description: The type of this event.

item_prototype.name: Unit Event Unit Id for {#EVENTID}
item_prototype.description: The connUnitId of the connectivity unit that contains this event table.

item_prototype.name: Unit Event Time for {#EVENTID}
item_prototype.description: This is the real time when the event occurred. It has the following format. DDMMYYYY HHMMSS DD=day number MM=month number YYYY=year number HH=hour number MM=minute number SS=seconds number If not applicable, return a NULL string.

item_prototype.name: UnitS Event Time for {#EVENTID}
item_prototype.description: This is the sysuptime timestamp when the event occurred.

discovery_rule.name: connUnitLinkEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An entry describing a particular link to another.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkAgentAddressTypeY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: If connUnitLinkAgentAddressY is nonzero, it is a protocol address. ConnUnitLinkAgentAddressTypeY is the the 'address family number' assigned by IANA to identify the address format. (eg, 1 is Ipv4, 2 is Ipv6).

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkAgentAddressY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The address of an FCMGMT MIB agent for the node identified by connUnitLinkNodeIdY, if known; otherwise 16 octets of binary 0

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkAgentPortY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The IP port number for the agent. This is provided in case the agent is at a non-standard SNMP port.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkConnIdY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This is the Fibre Channel ID of this port. If the connectivity unit is a switch, this is expected to be a Big Endian value of 24 bits. If this is loop, then it is the ALPA that is connected. If this is an eport, then it will only contain the domain ID. If not any of those, unknown or cascaded loop, return all bits set to 1.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkIndex for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: This value is used to create a unique value for each entry in the link table with the same connUnitLinkUnitId. The value can only be reused if it is not currently in in use and the value is the next candidate to be used. This value is allowed to wrap at the highest value represented by the number of bits. This value is reset to zero when the system is Reset and the first value to be used is one.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkNodeIdX for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The node WWN of the unit at one end of the link. If the node WWN is unknown and the node is a connUnit in the responding agent then the value of this object MUST BE equal to its connUnitID.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkNodeIdY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The node WWN of the unit at the other end of the link. If the node WWN is unknown and the node is a connUnit in the responding SNMP agency then the value of this object MUST BE equal to its connUnitID.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkPortNumberX for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The port number on the unit specified by connUnitLinkNodeIdX if known, otherwise -1. If the value is nonnegative then it will be equal to connUnitPortPhysicalNumber.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkPortNumberY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The port number on the unit specified by connUnitLinkNodeIdY if known, otherwise -1. If the value is nonnegative then it will be equal to connUnitPortPhysicalNumber.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkPortWwnX for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The port WWN of the unit specified by connUnitLinkNodeIdX if known, otherwise 16 octets of binary 0

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkPortWwnY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The port WWN on the unit specified by connUnitLinkNodeIdY if known, otherwise 16 octets of binary 0

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkUnitId for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The connUnitId of the connectivity unit that contains this link table.

item_prototype.name: connUnitLinkUnitTypeY for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: Type of the FC connectivity unit as defined in connUnitType.

discovery_rule.name: Unit Port Discovery
discovery_rule.description: Each entry contains the information for a specific port.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Control for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: This object is used to control the addressed connUnit's port. Valid commands are: resetConnUnitPort: If the addressed connUnit allows this operation to be performed to this port, the addressed port performs a vendor-specific 'reset' operation. Examples of these operations are: the Link Reset protocol, the Loop Initialization protocol, or a resynchronization occurring between the transceiver in the addressed port to the transceiver that the port is connected to. bypassConnUnitPort: If the addressed connUnit allows this operation to be performed to this port, the addressed port performs a vendor-specific 'bypass' operation. Examples of these operations are: transitioning from online to offline, a request(NON-PARTICIPATING) command to the Loop Port state machine, or removal of the port from an arbitrated loop by a hub. unbypassConnUnitPort: If the addressed connUnit allows this operation to be performed to this port, the addressed port performs a vendor-specific 'unbypass' operation. Examples of these operations are: the Link Failure protocol, a request(PARTICIPATING) command to the Loop Port state machine, or addition of the port to an arbitrated loop by a hub. offlineConnUnitPort: If the addressed connUnit allows this operation to be performed to this port, the addressed port performs a vendor-specific 'offline' operation. Examples of these operations are: disabling a port's transceiver, the Link Failure protocol, request(NON-PARTICIPATING) command to the Loop Port state machine, or removal of the port from an arbitrated loop by a hub. onlineConnUnitPort: If the addressed connUnit allows this operation to be performed to this port, the addressed port performs a vendor-specific 'online' operation. Examples of these operations are: enabling a port's transceiver, the Link Failure protocol, request(PARTICIPATING) command to the Loop Port state machine, or addition of the port from an arbitrated loop by a hub. NOTE: Each implementation may chose not to allow any or all of these values on a SET.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port FC Class Capability for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: Bit mask that specifies the classes of service capability of this port. If this is not applicable, return all bits set to zero. The bits have the following definition: unknown - 0 class-f - 1 class-one - 2 class-two - 4 class-three - 8 class-four - 16 class-five - 32 class-six - 64

item_prototype.name: Unit Port FC Id for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: This is the assigned Fibre Channel ID of this port. This value is expected to be a Big Endian value of 24 bits. If this is loop, then it is the ALPA that is connected. If this is an eport, then it will only contain the domain ID left justified, zero filled. If this port does not have a Fibre Channel address, return all bits set to 1.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Index for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: A unique value among all connUnitPortEntrys on this connectivity unit, between 0 and connUnitNumPort[connUnitPortUnitId].

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Module Type for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: The module type of the port connector.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Name for {#CONNUNITPORTINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A string describing the addressed port.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Speed for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: The speed of the port in kilobytes per second.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port State for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: The state of the port hardware.

trigger_prototype.name: Port state for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME} is not ok

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Status for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: An overall protocol status for the port.

trigger_prototype.name: Port status for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME} is not ok

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Transmitter Type for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: The technology of the port transceiver.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Type for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: The port type.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Wwn for {#CONNUNITPORTNAME}
item_prototype.description: The World Wide Name of the port if applicable, otherwise empty string.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Statistic Fabric Count Error for {#CONNUNITPORTSTATFABRICINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A count of the errors that have occured on this port.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Statistic Fabric Count Rx Frame for {#CONNUNITPORTSTATFABRICINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of frames that have been received by this port.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Statatistic Fabric Count Rx Octets for {#CONNUNITPORTSTATFABRICINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of octets that have been received. by this port.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Statistic Fabric Count Tx Frame for {#CONNUNITPORTSTATFABRICINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of frames that have been transmitted by this port.

item_prototype.name: Unit Port Statistic Fabric Count Tx Octets for {#CONNUNITPORTSTATFABRICINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of octets that have been transmitted by this port.

discovery_rule.name: Unit Sensor Discovery
discovery_rule.description: Each entry contains the information for a specific sensor.

item_prototype.name: Unit Sensor Characteristic for {#CONNUNITSENSORNAME}
item_prototype.description: The characteristics being monitored by this sensor.

item_prototype.name: Unit Sensor Info for {#CONNUNITSENSORNAME}
item_prototype.description: Miscellaneous static info about the sensor such as its serial number.

item_prototype.name: Unit Sensor Message for {#CONNUNITSENSORNAME}
item_prototype.description: This describes the status of the sensor as a message. It may also provide more resolution on the sensor indication, for example 'Cover temperature 1503K, above nominal operating range'

item_prototype.name: Unit Sensor Status for {#CONNUNITSENSORNAME}
item_prototype.description: The status indicated by the sensor.

item_prototype.name: Unit Sensor Type for {#CONNUNITSENSORNAME}
item_prototype.description: The type of component being monitored by this sensor.

discovery_rule.name: Unit Interface Discovery
discovery_rule.description: An interface entry containing objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Admin Status for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Discards for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Errors for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Last Change for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Mtu for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Operational Status for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Output Discards for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Output Errors for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Physical Address for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The interface's address at the protocol layer immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Speed for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth.

item_prototype.name: Unit Interface Type for {#IFNAME}
item_prototype.description: The type of interface, distinguished according to the physical/link protocol(s) immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack.

discovery_rule.name: ipAddrEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: The addressing information for one of this entity's IP addresses.

item_prototype.name: ipAdEntAddr for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

item_prototype.name: ipAdEntBcastAddr for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The value of the least-significant bit in the IP broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. For example, when the Internet standard all-ones broadcast address is used, the value will be 1. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface.

item_prototype.name: ipAdEntIfIndex for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

item_prototype.name: ipAdEntNetMask for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

item_prototype.name: ipAdEntReasmMaxSize for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagrams received on this interface.
